{"author":"Joe Oakhart","author_email":"joeoakhart+bot@navapbc.com","author_id":"594c-9dcf-5ad6-4e6d","author_sig":"{\"payload\": \"\", \"payloadType\": \"application/vnd.rebar.authorship.v1+json\", \"signatures\": [{\"keyid\": \"594c-9dcf-5ad6-4e6d\", \"sig\": \"\"}]}","data":{"fields":{"description":"# Add the close-time plan-review gate\n\n## Goal\nPrevent an implemented ticket from closing after its own plan or a pinned upstream plan changed during execution, without running plan review inside close or invalidating every implementation because implementation files changed.\n\n## Implementation\n- This story is implemented only after its declared dependencies: 75de supplies `PlanValidityProfile.CLOSE`, `compute_validity(..., profile=...)`, pin health/enforcement, and additive validity results; 5967 supplies signed review phase/floor and phase compatibility. Those interfaces are feature-branch deliverables and are not present on current main before the predecessors land. Do not wire close until both predecessor implementations are available.\n- Register `require_plan_review_for_close: bool = False` on `_config_schema.py::VerifyConfig`, add the bool coercer to `_SECTIONS[\"verify\"]`, and update the config-surface golden. Default false preserves every existing close path and performs no signature or plan-material reads.\n- Add `_commands/gates.py::close_plan_review_gate_check(ticket_id, ticket_state, *, repo_root) -> dict` as the sole close policy boundary. It calls `signing.verify_signature(kind=\"plan-review\")`, then 75de's `compute_validity(..., kind=\"plan-review\", profile=PlanValidityProfile.CLOSE)`. CLOSE intentionally disables only code freshness (verified HEAD and per-file dependency hashes) because implementation changes are expected during execution; signature, reopen, registry, current own material, 5967 phase compatibility, and configured pin enforcement remain active. This cannot reuse `claim_gate_check`, because DEFAULT intentionally blocks code drift while CLOSE must not.\n- The helper runs only when `verify.require_plan_review_for_close=true` and the ticket is a task/story/epic taking the normal close path. It returns `{ok, verdict, reason}` and never invokes a model or network. `verify.enforce_plan_material_pins` controls only whether pin health invalidates; phase incompatibility, own-material drift, reopen, registry, signature, and malformed metadata always invalidate. Any unexpected local read/parser/signature exception is caught and returned fail-closed as verdict `unavailable`.\n- In `transition_close.close_ticket`, after structural/exemption/force checks and before `_completion_precheck`, reduce current state and call `close_plan_review_gate_check`. Failure raises the normal command error before completion verification with exact message `plan-review close gate: <verdict>: <reason>. Run rebar review-plan <canonical-id> separately, then retry close.` The verdict is the exact `compute_validity` verdict (`unsigned`, `stale-reopened`, `stale-regver`, `stale-material`, `unverifiable-material`, `stale-pin-drift`, `stale-pin-missing`, `malformed-pin`, `incompatible-phase`, `malformed-phase`, or `unavailable`); reason is diagnostic only. Close never launches `review-plan` itself.\n- Extend `txn.transition_core(..., *, pre_status_check: Callable[[Mapping[str, Any]], None] | None = None)` as a generic local pre-append hook; every existing caller defaults `None`. After acquiring the existing global write lock, re-reading state, verifying expected status, and applying structural close rules—but immediately before appending STATUS—invoke the callback with that freshly reduced state. A raised `RebarError` aborts the transaction and releases the lock without append/commit. `txn.py` imports no plan-review code.\n- When close enforcement applies, `close_ticket` passes a closure as `pre_status_check`; the closure calls the same pure `close_plan_review_gate_check` on the locked fresh state and raises the same command error on failure. This is the second check, not pre-existing txn behavior. It runs inside the single existing critical section; `close_ticket` never acquires a second lock. A signature, ticket, phase, own-material, or related-pin change between precheck and lock is therefore caught before STATUS append.\n- Preserve existing scope and bypass rules: bugs, session logs, code reviews, identities, and idea→closed remain exempt exactly as the claim gate; a non-empty force-close reason bypasses both completion verification and this plan-review gate and retains its audit event; structural child-closure rules are never bypassed. `close_ticket` remains the sole production task/story/epic close entry point, and all CLI/library/MCP surfaces inherit the behavior.\n- Document the CLOSE profile policy, flag interaction, error/remediation vocabulary, locked callback, and force/exemption behavior in advanced `docs/plan-review-gate.md`.\n\n## Acceptance Criteria\n- [ ] With `require_plan_review_for_close=false` or absent, normal close behavior is byte-for-byte equivalent and performs no plan-review reads.\n- [ ] With enforcement enabled, task/story/epic close runs the plan gate before completion verification.\n- [ ] CLOSE accepts certified, registry-current, material-current, phase-compatible reviews despite HEAD or file-dependency drift.\n- [ ] Unsigned, reopened, stale-registry, own-material drift, malformed metadata, and phase incompatibility block even when pin enforcement is false.\n- [ ] Pin drift/missing/malformed blocks only when `enforce_plan_material_pins=true`; disabled enforcement remains advisory.\n- [ ] Every failure uses the exact verdict-prefixed message and separate `review-plan` remediation; unexpected exceptions fail closed as `unavailable` without traceback.\n- [ ] Close performs zero plan-review LLM/model/network calls.\n- [ ] The generic `pre_status_check` runs under the existing lock after fresh state/structural checks and before STATUS append.\n- [ ] A failing locked callback appends and commits no STATUS event.\n- [ ] A plan/signature/phase/material/pin change between precheck and lock is rejected by the locked recheck.\n- [ ] Existing transition callers that omit `pre_status_check` are unchanged.\n- [ ] Bugs, session logs, code reviews, identities, and idea→closed retain their existing exemptions.\n- [ ] Non-empty force-close reason bypasses both gates with the existing audit trail but never bypasses structural child closure.\n- [ ] `docs/plan-review-gate.md` documents the CLOSE policy, both flags, callback ordering, error vocabulary, and bypass scope.\n\n## Verification\n- `pytest -q tests/unit/test_plan_review_close_gate.py` proves the full validity/verdict/config matrix, code-drift exclusion, fail-closed exceptions, and zero-model behavior.\n- `pytest -q tests/interfaces/lifecycle/test_plan_review_gate.py tests/interfaces/lifecycle/test_completion_gate.py` proves precheck ordering, public close behavior, default-off compatibility, and remediation messages.\n- `pytest -q tests/interfaces/lifecycle/test_transition_pre_status_check.py` proves inside-lock ordering, race rejection, and no-write callback failure.\n- `pytest -q tests/interfaces/lifecycle/test_idea_close_bypass.py tests/interfaces/lifecycle/test_attested_signing.py` updates existing exemption/force/signing ordering assertions.\n- `pytest -q tests/unit/test_plan_review_docs.py tests/interfaces/contracts/test_config_surface.py` proves advanced documentation and config registration/golden coverage.\n- Run `make check` and the full non-LLM test suite.\n"}},"env_id":"ade0f2ef-51cc-45a2-bb97-c09846cd3df5","event_type":"EDIT","timestamp":1784558396721656001,"uuid":"ac8a7f3e-bb87-480a-9a2d-ea84f39e8404"}